docs.title: cms-gov-provider-data-sdk
docs.text: This project demonstrates use of oapi to generate an SDK/client for the Center for Medicare & Medicaid Services provider data API.

docs.title: Install
docs.text:
You can install this package from Github with pip:

pip3 install git+https://github.com/davebelais/cms-gov-provider-data-sdk.git@main#egg=cms_gov_provider_data_sdk

Currently, I have no plans to distribute this package to PYPI, as adequate support would be cumbersome without additional API access and a sandbox or test environment—but "watch" this repo if you'd like to know if the status of development changes.

docs.title: Contributing to cms-gov-provider-data-sdk
docs.text: Please note that you must have hatch installed prior to performing the following steps.

docs.title: For Contributors and Code Owners
docs.text:
1. Install hatch

  2. Clone and Install

    To install this project for development of this library, clone this repository (replacing "~/Code", below, with the directory under which you want your project to reside), then run make:

    cd ~/Code && \
git clone\
github.com/davebelais/cms-gov-provider-data-sdk.git cms-gov-provider-data-sdk && \
cd cms-gov-provider-data-sdk && \
make

  3. Create a new branch for your changes (replacing "descriptive-branch-name" with a descriptive branch name):

    git branch descriptive-branch-name

  4. Make some changes.

  5. Format and lint your code:

    make format

  6. Test your changes:

    make test

  7. Push your changes and create a pull request.

docs.title: For Everyone Else
docs.text: If you are not a contributor on this project, you can still create pull requests, however you will need to fork this project, push changes to your fork, and create a pull request from your forked repository.
